[2] USA (Washington)
Date: Thu 2 Nov 2017
Source: iFIBER One News [edited]
http://www.ifiberone.com/columbia_basin/mumps-and-whooping-cough-a-problem-in/youtube_71b3dcd4-c002-11e7-9a61-ff27becf4d65.html


Grant County [Washington] saw an extraordinary amount of mumps cases this year [2017] with 45. The mumps outbreak was contained to the Columbia Basin Job Corps and the Ephrata School District. Grant County Health District's Theresa Atkinson says that was a fraction of the 888 cases reported statewide.

"The mumps outbreak was incredibly large for our area," said Adkinson Fortunately, no one currently has mumps in Grant County.

The same cannot be said about whooping cough with 78 current cases in the county. This year [2017], Moses Lake had 54 cases of pertussis, Ephrata had 22, Soap Lake 2 and both Royal City and Warden had 1.

"It's the largest pertussis outbreak we've ever experienced," said Adkinson.

For more on how to prevent these illnesses, go to http://granthealth.org.

